metadata.notes: To change your nonimmigrant status in the U.S., you (or your employer) must file a request with USCIS using the appropriate form before your authorized stay expires
metadata.text:
**Specific Restrictions:**
*   **Vocational student (M-1):** Cannot change to F-1 (academic student) or any H status if the M-1 training provided qualifications for the H position.
*   **Exchange visitor (J-1):** Cannot change status if admitted for graduate medical training (unless a special waiver is obtained) or if subject to the foreign residence requirement (unless a waiver is obtained). Without a waiver, J-1s can only change to A or G visa categories.

This document outlines the regulations and procedures for practical training (PT) available to F-1 (academic) and M-1 (vocational) nonimmigrant students in the United States. Practical training allows students to gain employment experience directly related to their major area of study
metadata.text:
*   **Timing:** Occurs before the program end date, can be part-time or full-time.
*   **Limitations:** One year or more of full-time CPT at the same educational level makes a student ineligible for post-completion Optional Practical Training (OPT).
*   **Eligibility:** Must have completed one full academic year (with exceptions for certain graduate programs), be enrolled full-time, obtain DSO endorsement, and participate in an approved program.

**I. F-1 Student Curricular Practical Training (CPT):**
*   **Definition:** Alternative work-study, cooperative education, or required internships/practicums offered through school-employer cooperative agreements, integral to an established curriculum.
*   **Authorization:** No USCIS application or Employment Authorization Document (EAD) (Form I-766) is required. Authorization is granted by the student's Designated School Official (DSO) and annotated on Form I-20.
